To create a preview element that shows a real-time copy of the content within your region-of-interest (ROI) frame as the DOM is manipulated, you can use JavaScript along with the MutationObserver API. Here's how you can achieve this:

1. First, create the ROI frame and the preview element in your HTML file:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Real-time DOM Preview</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="roiFrame">
        <!-- Your region-of-interest content goes here -->
    </div>
    <div id="preview">
        <!-- This is where the preview will be displayed -->
    </div>
    <script src="main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
1. Next, create a JavaScript file, `main.js`, to handle the real-time preview functionality:
```javascript
// Get the ROI frame and preview element
const roiFrame = document.getElementById('roiFrame');
const preview = document.getElementById('preview');

// Function to clone the content of the ROI frame and update the preview element
function updatePreview() {
    // Clone the ROI frame
    const clonedRoiFrame = roiFrame.cloneNode(true);

    // Remove any existing content in the preview element
    while (preview.firstChild) {
        preview.firstChild.remove();
    }

    // Insert the cloned ROI frame into the preview element
    preview.appendChild(clonedRoiFrame);
}

// Initialize the MutationObserver to listen for changes in the ROI frame
const observer = new MutationObserver((mutationsList, observer) => {
    // Call the updatePreview function whenever a change is detected
    updatePreview();
});

// Configure the observer to watch for changes in the entire subtree, including attributes and child elements
const config = { childList: true, subtree: true, attributes: true };

// Start the observer
observer.observe(roiFrame, config);

// Update the preview element initially
updatePreview();
```
Now, whenever there is a change in the DOM of your ROI frame, the preview element will automatically update to reflect those changes.

