```
This updated configuration will now listen for changes in the `style` attribute, which should cover size and position changes. With these changes, the preview element should update in real-time to reflect any modifications to elements within the ROI frame, including changes to size and position.

To improve the efficiency of the deleting process, you can remove the MutationObserver's call to `while (preview.firstChild) { preview.firstChild.remove(); }` when removing existing content from the preview element. Instead, use the `replaceChildren` method, which is faster and more efficient than looping through each child node. Here's the updated `updatePreview()` function in the `main.js` script:

```javascript
function updatePreview() {
    // Clone the ROI frame
    const clonedRoiFrame = roiFrame.cloneNode(true);

    // Replace the existing content in the preview element with the cloned ROI frame
    preview.replaceChildren(clonedRoiFrame);
}
