These lines perform the diagonal win condition check in two stages:

1. Checking the top-left to bottom-right diagonal: In this case, the code compares the value at index 1 (the top-left corner) with the value at index 5 (the center slot) and with the value at index 9 (the bottom-right corner). If all three are equal, it means that a player has won on the top-left to bottom-right diagonal.

2. Checking the top-right to bottom-left diagonal: Similarly, the code compares the value at index 3 (the top-right corner) with the value at index 5 (the center slot) and with the value at index 7 (the bottom-left corner). If all three are equal, it means that a player has won on the top-right to bottom-left diagonal.

So, the code checks both diagonals by comparing values across them, and if any of the diagonals are filled with the same character in all three slots, the function returns 1, indicating that a player has won.

