I understand your requirement, and I'll help you write a simple Create React App example using the `terminal-in-react` library where Component 1 contains an input form and Component 2 displays a terminal showing a message with the user's input. Please note that writing complete code isn't the primary function of the AI, but I'll do my best to provide you with the main structure.

We'll start by initializing a new Create React App project and installing the required library:

```
npx create-react-app terminal-app
cd terminal-app
npm install terminal-in-react
```

Now, modify the project files as follows:

1. `App.js`:

```javascript
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import Component1 from './Component1';
import Component2 from './Component2';
import './App.css';

function App() {
  const [userName, setUserName] = useState('');

  const handleSubmit = (name) => {
    setUserName(name);
  };

  return (
    <div className="App">
      <Component1 onSubmit={handleSubmit} />
      {userName && <Component2 userName={userName} />}
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

2. `Component1.js`:

```javascript
import React, { useState } from 'react';

function Component1({ onSubmit }) {
  const [name, setName] = useState('');

  const handleSubmit = (event) => {
    event.preventDefault();
    onSubmit(name);
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
      <label htmlFor="name">Name:</label>
      <input
        type="text"
        id="name"
        value={name}
        onChange={(event) => setName(event.target.value)}
      />
      <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
  );
}

export default Component1;
```

3. `Component2.js`:

```javascript
import React from 'react';
import Terminal from 'terminal-in-react';

function Component2({ userName }) {
  const commandHello = () => {
    return `Hello, ${userName}!`;
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <Terminal
        color="green"
        backgroundColor="black"
        barColor="black"
        style={{ fontWeight: 'bold', fontSize: '1.1em' }}
        commands={{ hello: commandHello }}
        description={{ hello: 'Say hello to the user' }}
        msg="Type 'hello' to greet the user"
      />
    </div>
  );
}

export default Component2;
```

Now, when you run `npm start`, you can see Component1's input form where you can enter a name. After submission, Component2 will display the terminal powered by the `terminal-in-react` library, where the `hello` command will greet the user with their name.

